Sentencas: Kinetics of oxygen reaction in porous La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-delta (LSCF) and La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-delta-Ce0.8Gd0.2O1.9 (LSCF-GDC) electrodes are systematically studied.
Titulo: Kinetics of oxygen reaction in porous La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ-Ce0.8Gd0.2O1.9 composite electrodes for solid oxide cells

Sentencas: Normally, there are two pathways of oxygen reaction in porous LSCF: in reaction region with oxygen exchanging at electrode/air interface, and around electrode/electrolyte interface with oxygen exchanging at electrode/electrolyte/air triple-phase boundary (TPB).
Titulo: Kinetics of oxygen reaction in porous La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ-Ce0.8Gd0.2O1.9 composite electrodes for solid oxide cells

Sentencas: GDC in porous LSCF-GDC accelerates oxygen transport and oxygen gas diffusion during oxygen reaction.
Titulo: Kinetics of oxygen reaction in porous La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ-Ce0.8Gd0.2O1.9 composite electrodes for solid oxide cells

Sentencas: In addition, because the formation of LSCF/GDC interface increases the length of TPB and affects the geometry of reaction region, oxygen reaction in LSCF-GDC tends to proceed in the TPB pathway.
Titulo: Kinetics of oxygen reaction in porous La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ-Ce0.8Gd0.2O1.9 composite electrodes for solid oxide cells

Sentencas: The performance and oxygen reactions of LSCF-GDC are evaluated at 650 degrees C and 850 degrees C. Oxygen reaction in LSCF-GDC is suppressed by CO2, but increasing GDC content is able to improve the CO2 tolerance of electrode.
Titulo: Kinetics of oxygen reaction in porous La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ-Ce0.8Gd0.2O1.9 composite electrodes for solid oxide cells

Sentencas: Though the performance reduction by H2O is unobvious, H2O can aggravate CO2 degradation at low temperature.
Titulo: Kinetics of oxygen reaction in porous La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ-Ce0.8Gd0.2O1.9 composite electrodes for solid oxide cells
